<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-10-31T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-10-31T15:00:00-05:00" n="849" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d849">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/6287:
                                Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Consul General at Beirut</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Palmer</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-10-31T15:00:00-05:00">October 31, 1940—3 p.m.</date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>87. The Chargé d’Affaires at Vichy in reporting on French reaction to
                                the Italian attack on Greece<note n="37" xml:id="d849fn37">Telegram
                                    No. 845, October 28, 9 p.m., not printed.</note> states: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                    <p>“It is privately admitted in certain official circles that if
                                        Turkey is drawn in, the allegiance of Syria to the Vichy
                                        regime will promptly be severed.”</p>
                                </quote>
                            </p>
                            <p>Please comment.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>